.TH simple_shell 1 "January 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX shell designed to execute commands and handle basic shell functionality. It supports interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH USAGE

.TP
.B Interactive Mode:
Run the shell and execute commands directly.

Example:
.EXAMPLE
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ pwd
$ exit
.EE

.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode:
Feed commands through a pipe or from a file.

Example:
.EXAMPLE
echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
cat commands.txt | ./hsh
.EE

.SH FEATURES
- Displays a prompt and waits for user input.
- Executes commands with or without arguments.
- Searches for commands in the user's PATH.
- Handles built-in commands like \fBexit\fP and \fBenv\fP.
- Supports interactive and non-interactive modes.
- Manages errors such as "command not found."

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.TP
.B env
Displays the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode example:
.EXAMPLE
$ ./hsh
$ ls
main.c shell.c shell.h
$ env
USER=julien
HOME=/home/julien
PATH=/usr/bin:/bin
$ exit
.EE

.TP
Non-interactive mode example:
.EXAMPLE
echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
main.c shell.c shell.h
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2)
